1.Customer queries (questions, issues, complaints)

Support agent responses (solutions, replies, instructions)

Conversational context (multi-turn dialogues, follow-ups)

Domain-specific FAQs and knowledge bases

Here are some suitable datasets (free and paid) you can explore:

General Customer Support Datasets:
Customer Support on Twitter Dataset (by Kaggle)

Contains customer support conversations from Twitter (brands like Apple, Amazon, etc.).

Link: https://www.kaggle.com/thoughtvector/customer-support-on-twitter

2.DSTC (Dialog State Tracking Challenge) Datasets

Multi-turn dialogues for different domains, including customer service.

Link: https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/project/dialog-state-tracking-challenge/

3.MultiWOZ Dataset

Large-scale multi-domain task-oriented dialogue dataset (hotel booking, restaurant, etc.).

Link: https://www.cambridge.org/datasets/multiwoz

4.Ubuntu Dialogue Corpus

Technical support dialogues in the Ubuntu domain (can adapt for tech-related support bots).

Link: https://github.com/rkadlec/ubuntu-ranking-dataset-creator

5.Microsoft Customer Support Dataset (from Azure)

Contains anonymized customer support transcripts.

